The available skull (PG 95/1502a) is almost completely preserved (
Fig. 1
). The face is short (M3 at the level of the anterior third of the orbit) and slightly bent relative to the braincase. Because of the preservation status it is not clear whether there is a lachrymal fossa, but there is an ethmoid fissure. The premaxillary bones are in contact with the nasals. The width of the

